page.title: 03HOUSING - KEYINGHAM
page.content: Keyingham is the larger of the two villages having a population of 2250 and is still expanding, although building is restricted by local authority planning groups. New development is usually groups of houses three bedroomed semidetached with a garage and central heating costing around Â£25,000. Most of the families occupying these houses travel to Hull the nearest city to work, only a very small percentage of the residents of Keyingham and Ottringham actually work in or around the villages. There is a small estate of council houses, these are owned and maintained by the local council and can be rented.
